   giants were obtained with the CCD camera in the coude spectrograph of
   the Shajn telescope. The effective temperatures T(ef) of these giants
   have been determined from (Y-K) colors, and the gravities 1g g have been
   obtained from the comparison of observed and calculated equivalent
   widths if MgH features with the wavelengths 5134,6; 5138,7, 5140,2
   angstrom angstrom. The results of the investigation of the influence of
   some parameters (micro- and macroturbulence, metallicity, abundance of
   Mg etc.) on the calculated MgH line profiles are discussed. The values
   of T(ef) and Ig g are compared with those obtained by other methods and
   published ones. The calibration diagrams for the determination of
   gravities of red giants with T(ef) from 4000 K to 5000 K from the
   equivalent widths and the central intensities of MgH lines are proposed.},
Journal-ISO = {Astron. Zhurnal},
}

@article{ 92Kuxxxx.MgH,
